    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Aden: An assessment by a humanitarian partner in Tuban district, Lahj governorate, found that 65 per cent of the estimated 729 displaced households in the governorate were from Al Hudaydah and 26 per cent from Taizz. More than half of the IDPs are women. Only 46 per cent of the assessed population have access to drinking water and to personal hygiene facilities. Another assessment conducted in four districts of Shabwah governorate (As Said, Habban, Ataq and Nisab) found that half of the displaced children are not attending school, exposing them to the risk of early marriage, child labour, recruitment and other types of exploitation."/>
